<tr><td colspan=2 Bgcolor=#000000 Align=center><font color=white size=+2>our karma system (NT)</font>
</td></tr><tr><td width=10% Bgcolor=#101010 Align=center Valign=top><table width=200><tr><td align=center><font size=-1><table><tr><td align=center><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_top.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_left.jpg><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/portraits/NEKEDHEALER.jpg width="104" height="184"><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_right.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_bottom.jpg></td></tr></table>Legendary  NEKEDHEALER REPLACEROFLIFE<br>Level 61 Cleric<br><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_11.gif" title="Silver Order of Leadership"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_7.gif" title="Star of Achievement"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_6.gif" title="Order of Meritorious Service"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_16.gif" title="Service Star Cluster"><br>Webmaster<br><a style="text-decoration:none;" href="main.cgi?fetch=NEKEDHEALER"><font size=-1 color="#DDDDDD">NEKEDHEALER</font></a><font size=-1>'S LINEAGE</font><br><img src='http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/bio.gif' border=0></font></td></tr></table></td><td width=90% Valign=top><a href=main.cgi?followup=188&forum=4><p align=right><font color=#cccccc>Reply | </a><a href=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/guild-builder/call/main.cgi?action=messages&forum=4><font color=#cccccc>Return</a></p><br clear=all><p><i>this originally posted by jeptha but we want it available to non-guildies also. :)<br><br><br>First of all, getting used to the idea of USING karma is going to be different for us all, but it will help in building the guild stronger and here is why : <br><br>U have to earn loot that drops, and im talking about the good stuff here. <br><br>To earn karma all u need to do is participate. If u play often and participate in guild functions, then points will not be a problem for u. Which means that this will eliminate those who join our guild just to get loot then leave.<br><br>In other words, those who are active and helping to build the guild will be rewarding themselves with better armor and weapons so the guild will grow stronger.<br><br>In a side note, i will be thoroughly pissed if i see someone trying to sell loot given by way of karma on raids. The purpose is to build the guild, not fatten your bank. We want u to get the good stuff and use it. If u do this, u are taking away loot that someone else wanted to help themselves be better for the guild.<br><br><br>OK, now this is how KARMA is going to work :<br>1) Attending scheduled raids ... 10pts<br>2) Leading Raid ... 50pts<br>3) Important Roll in raid ... puller, main healer, MA, and main slower ... 20pts<br>4) Other acts of heroism or raid saving actions, (determined by officers or raid leader only) ... 25pts<br>5) Attending a "last moment raid/mini raid" ... 10pts, the reason for this being the same as scheduled raids is, its alot harder to leave an xp group or friends to help someone with .. epic mob etc. than it is to know about it and be ready for it.<br>6) Other acts of kindness shown inside or out of the guild and nominated by guild members.<br><br>This system may go through minor changes or tweeks as the officers see fit and pls give me all your suggestions/criticism so that way this may be done for the benefit of the guild. I will be very open minded to your opinions but pls keep in mind that the officers have final say in decisions made concerning this system.<br><br>This is where we find out how we can USE or LOSE our KARMA. <br><br>1) KARMA will be assigned to loot drops in raids and u can chose to use that assigned amount if u get into the random and win the loot. The officers will assign the amount of KARMA per item when the loot is being randomed. <br>EX: In a Kael raid a Chain BP mq drops, the officers may decide to assign 40 KARMA points to it, that is when u may decide to enter the random and use your 40 KP (KARMA points) to win the BP, obviously if u don't win the random then u don't lose the KP; or u can chose to stay out of random and save for another time for better armor ... etc. Now as the table in the KARMA section has stated that 40kp is equivilent to attending 4 raids. So u see how u must make your decision. Again this was just an example.<br><br>2) Kp can also be USED to hold quest/epic raids for yourself if u are working on them and need the help of the guild for a large scail raid where it must be planned out. This is NOT talking about random 1 group "put together" fights. U can contact Nifel or myself on this matter and we will confer on what it will take and how long it will take and we will get back to u with a Kp amount.<br><br>3) Kp can be LOST if u don't read the boards often enough like what is stated in the MERIT section of the website here. The reason for that is because if u don't read it then u won't know what is going on for raids/functions that we may be holding; therefore, not participating to help make the guild stronger.<br><br>Again, I stress, this system is for the building of the guild. If u participate Kp will come your way. It is also used as a security measure for those who are just in it for the loot, they will have to earn it. Epics can cause people to take advantage of the guild to gain the help and then leave ... u don't know how many times i have seen that in this guild and in others. So, if u have the Kp to use towards it then u have earned the gratitude of the guild to help u out in your epic adventure. There is an exception to this: the CLERIC epic is a MUST for the guild to have during raids so no Kp will be used for this quest. I hope u all agree with me on this one. If u believe that your epic is just as needed for the guild, then talk to an officer and state your case concerning this. <br><br>This system is new and will probably go through changes or tweeks as we go foward and learn it. Any suggestions/criticisms are welcome so that we may perfect it for the betterment of the guild. Pls keep in mind that the officers have final say in this area.<br><br>Remember this game is to be fun, thats why we all are here and being apart of a family makes it easier to do so.<br><br>Jeptha<br>61 Paladin<br>Karma Priest/Assistant Raid Officer<br><br>--posted by neked by cut and paste :)<br><br><br clear=all><br><font size=-2>(Edited by NEKEDHEALER on 7/2/2003 at 1:36p.m.)</font><br><font size=-2>(Edited by NEKEDHEALER on 7/2/2003 at 1:35p.m.)</font><br></i><br></td></tr><tr><td>
